.TH SUTURE-SWITCH "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-switch \- Switch to a different branch (modern alternative to checkout)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture switch [\\fIoptions\\fR] [\\fIbranch\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Switch to a different branch (modern alternative to checkout).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-c, \\\-\\\-create \\fI<name>\\fR
Create a new branch before switching
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture switch main          # Switch to "main"
suture switch \\\-c feature   # Create and switch to "feature"
suture switch \\\-c feat main # Create "feat" from "main"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
